And this is the very point. Are you aware that by changing the scale from 60
miles/hex to 40 miles/hex you will have an immense map while still being
forced to look at it in a small 1024x768 window? It will be like playing the
old &quot;Fire in the East/Scorched Earth&quot; in the &quot;Europa&quot; series while looking
at the map only through a magnifying glass.

&quot;Monster&quot; wargames where the player must be able to conduct operational and
strategic operations in the... er... whole PTO *need* the possibility to
contemplate as much of the map as possible on screen in the planning phase -
maybe even whole sub-theatres. This happens in TOAW, where I'm now enjoying
monster scenarios at 1920x1200 and it is like looking at the old paper maps
on the cellar table.

IMHO, limiting this &quot;window&quot; to a fixed rez was a fundamental planning
mistake in WitP - and with a still bigger map the results will be still more
claustrophobic.
