Empires in Arms switches the screen resolution to 1024x768 - I can
live with that.

What I have trouble accepting is that when I &lt;alt&gt;&lt;tab&gt; to the Empires
in Arms manual, which was clearly designed for higher resolutions, the
resolution does not switch back to my default, but *stays* at
1024x768.

As Empires in Arms is programmed in Delphi I'd like to share with
everyone how bloody difficult this is to get right.

Below is the *complete* code of a demo app which switches the
resolution to 1024x768 for that app but which on &lt;alt&gt;&lt;tab&gt; or
minimize or whatever else which takes you out of the app switches your
screen resolution back to the default, and, of course, when you
&lt;alt&gt;&lt;tab&gt; back into the game or whatever changes it back to the
resolution the game prefers.

- start of code -

unit Main;

interface

uses
Windows, Messages, SysUtils, Variants, Classes, Graphics, Controls,
Forms, Dialogs, StdCtrls;

type
TfrmMain = class(TForm)
procedure FormClose(Sender: TObject; var Action: TCloseAction);
procedure FormCreate(Sender: TObject);
private
{ Private declarations }
Procedure ChangeResolution(iWidth: Integer; iHeight: Integer);
Procedure AppActivate(Sender: TObject);
Procedure AppDeActivate(Sender: TObject);
public
{ Public declarations }
OrigScreenHeight : Integer;
OrigScreenWidth : Integer;
end;

var
frmMain: TfrmMain;

implementation

{$R *.dfm}

procedure TfrmMain.FormCreate(Sender: TObject);
begin
// save the original setting
OrigScreenHeight := Screen.Height;
OrigScreenWidth := Screen.Width;
Application.OnActivate := AppActivate;
Application.OnDeActivate := AppDeActivate;
end;

procedure TfrmMain.FormClose(Sender: TObject; var Action:
TCloseAction);
begin
// change back to the original screen resolution
ChangeResolution (OrigScreenWidth,OrigScreenHeight);
end;

// Called when the app receives the focus
Procedure TFrmMain.AppActivate(Sender: TObject);
Begin
// Change to what the application needs
If ((Screen.Width &lt;&gt; 1024) or (Screen.Height &lt;&gt; 768)) Then
ChangeResolution(1024,768);
end;

// Called when the app loses focus
Procedure TfrmMain.AppDeActivate(Sender: TObject);
Begin
// Change to the default setting
ChangeResolution (OrigScreenWidth,OrigScreenHeight);
end;

// Actual procedure which changes the display resolution
procedure TfrmMain.ChangeResolution(iWidth: Integer; iHeight:
Integer);
var
a : Boolean;
i : LongInt;
DevM : TDEVMODE;
begin
i := 0;
With DevM Do
Begin
Repeat
a := EnumDisplaySettings(pchar(0), i, DevM);
i := i + 1;
Until (a = False);
End;
DevM.dmFields := DM_PELSWIDTH or DM_PELSHEIGHT;

DevM.dmPelsWidth := iWidth;
DevM.dmPelsHeight := iHeight;

ChangeDisplaySettings(DevM, 0);
end;

end.

- end of code

Took me half an hour to get it working and all of the above code was
either in the help file or on the 'Net. It's trivial to get it right,
so get it right. No excuses.

Greetz,

Eddy Sterckx
